<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-538] zookeeper.async causes python to segfault</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-538</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Henry, can you take a look at this, am I doing it right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;calling &lt;br/&gt;
        zookeeper.async(self.handle, path)&lt;br/&gt;
causes python to segfault.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;see: &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/phunt/zk-smoketest/blob/master/zk-smoketest.py&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://github.com/phunt/zk-smoketest/blob/master/zk-smoketest.py&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
